<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1856-05-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1856-05-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="184" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d184">
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Marcy</persName> to Mr.
                                        <persName type="to">Rowcroft</persName></hi>
                            </head>
                            <dateline><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of
                                        State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1856-05-28"><hi rend="italic">May</hi> 28,
                                1856</date>.</dateline>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: For reasons which have been
                                communicated to Her Majesty’s government, the President has revoked
                                the exequatur heretofore granted to you, by which you were permitted
                                to exercise the functions and enjoy the privileges of British consul
                                at Cincinnati.</p>
                            <p>I herewith send to you a copy of the act of revocation.</p>
                            <p><seg type="margin">[608]</seg> *In consequence of this proceeding,
                                the President has deemed it proper that the pending prosecution
                                against you, for the violation of the neutrality law of the United
                                States, should be discontinued.</p>
                            <p>Orders to that effect have been issued to the United States attorney
                                at Cincinnati.</p>
                            <p>I have the honor to be, your obedient servant,</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <list>
                                        <item>W. L. MARCY.</item>
                                        <item>Mr. <hi rend="smallcaps">Charles
                                                Rowcroft</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Her Britannic
                                                Majesty’s Consul, Cincinnati.</hi></item>
                                    </list>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>